 Here is an example of an XML mission plan based on your requirements:
```php
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<mission>
    <name>Pistachio Tree Photography</name>
    <description>Visit 5 pistachio trees in a row and take pictures of 3 of them.</description>
    <tasks>
        <task id="1">
            <name>Start at the farm</name>
            <action>Drive to the starting point</action>
        </task>
        <task id="2">
            <name>Visit Pistachio Tree 1</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="3">
            <name>Visit Pistachio Tree 2</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="4">
            <name>Visit Pistachio Tree 3</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="5">
            <name>Visit Pistachio Tree 4</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
        <task id="6">
            <name>Visit Pistachio Tree 5</name>
            <action>Take a picture of the tree</action>
        </task>
    </tasks>
</mission>
```
This XML file defines a mission with a name and description, followed by a list of tasks. Each task has an ID, name, and action associated with it. In this case, the actions are to drive to the starting point, visit each tree in order, and take pictures of 3 of them. You can modify the actions as needed for your specific requirements. 